    "description":  "A description of some of the benefits of the SIA\u0027s Approved Contractor Scheme.",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eOur Approved Contractor Scheme (ACS) can make your company stand out as one of the best providers of private security services in the UK. It can also give you valuable benefits that you can use in your day-to-day work.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"making-your-day-to-day-work-easier\"\u003eMaking your day-to-day work easier\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"licence-assist-and-licence-management\"\u003eLicence Assist and Licence Management\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOur Licence Assist and Licence Management services give you greater control over the licensing of your staff. Any approved contractor can use Licence Assist. However, you will need to meet extra requirements if you want to use Licence Management. You will also need to sign a legal agreement with us.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRead more about \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/use-our-business-services\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eLicence Assist and Licence Management\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"licence-dispensation-notices-ldns\"\u003eLicence Dispensation Notices (LDNs)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe can give approved contractors permission to use security staff while we are still processing their licence applications. This allows greater flexibility.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRead more about \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/licence-dispensation-notices-ldns-guidance-and-forms\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003elicence dispensation notices\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"business-opportunities\"\u003eBusiness opportunities\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe regularly tell buyers of private security services about the benefits of using an SIA approved contractor; these include local authorities, government departments, and the commercial sector. We have a \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.services.sia.homeoffice.gov.uk/Pages/acs-roac.aspx\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eregister of approved contractors\u003c/a\u003e on our website for buyers to check when they are choosing suppliers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"access-contracts-that-are-not-offered-to-other-companies\"\u003eAccess contracts that are not offered to other companies\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eACS approval is a requirement for many public contracts. For example, any contractor or sub-contractor providing security services under a Scottish Government contract must be ACS approved.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"advertising-your-acs-approval\"\u003eAdvertising your ACS approval\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYour company will be able to display the approved contractor plaque and certificate in your offices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou will also be able to add the ACS accreditation mark to your stationery, vehicles, and website. You can buy extra certified copies of your ACS certificate to include in your new business proposals, or to show to existing clients.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen you display the ACS accreditation mark, you will reassure your customers, prospects and employees that they have chosen to work with one of the very best security providers in the business.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou may even be able to use your ACS accreditation when you negotiate with your commercial insurance providers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"other-exclusive-benefits\"\u003eOther exclusive benefits\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe invite approved contractors to take part in regular regional forums led by us. We set these up to share best practice, talk about topical matters, and to give licensing and other updates. We give approved contractors regular updates about new developments affecting their business and the wider industry.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e",
